FBIS4-28101 "dreas110_a_94025" FBIS-EAS-94-110 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Ex-Im Bank Makes Loan for Thai Oil Refinery Ex-Im Bank Makes Loan for Thai Oil Refinery OW0706084994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0825 GMT 7 Jun 94 OW0706084994 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 7 KYODO -- The Export-Import Bank [Ex-Im Bank] of Japan said Tuesday [7 June] it has extended credit to Thailand's Start Petroleum Refining Co. for an amount not exceeding 334 million dollars. The Thai company will use the loan to purchase Japanese goods and services for building and operating an oil refinery in Map Ta Phu [place-name as received]. The International Finance Corp. and a syndicate of Japanese, American and European commercial banks will also provide credit for the project.
